Anxiety over mold is very common after floods. Mold isn’t good for you, but particulate matter and bleach are worse. Drying is the only solution, albeit a difficult one for many. Children and those with lung problems need to stay away during repairs and masks should be used.

It’s hard to dry insulation and often it’s easier to clean everything out to rebuild from the studs. Partially flooded structures will have mold growth even above the flood line. It’s ok to only remove the parts saturated by flood.

That's talking about a handful of families who chose not to use the best available prevention, putting other students at risk as they all attend in-person classes -- which are obviously beneficial and, indeed, necessary for good health.
